Chapter1
1.program:
	an executable file residing on disk ina directory.
2.process:
	an excuting instance of a program.
3.thread:
	the smallest unit of processing that can be  scheduled by an operating 
	system and contained inside a process.
4.POSIX:
	Portable Operating System Interface, IEEE standard for maintaining 
	compatibility between operating systems, formally designated as
	IEEE 1003.
5.system calls:
	all implementations of the operating system provide a well-defined, 
	limited number of entry points directly into the kernel.
6.library function:	
